Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Candente, Milpo, Minera IRL, Rio Alto

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-04-06T20:21:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/peru-stocks-atacocha-candente-milpo-minera-irl-rio-alto.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index rose 0.5 percent to 21,554.14. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index gained 0.1 percent to 2,923.70.  Gold miners gained after futures rose to a record in New
York, said Daniel Romero, an analyst at Lima-based investment
fund NC&F Inversiones SA.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold exploration
company, rose 3.6 percent to $2.30.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a
U.K. minerals explorer with a gold mine in Peru, gained 2.1
percent to $1.48.  Copper, zinc and silver miners advanced after metals gained
in New York and  London .  Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based
silver and zinc producer, climbed 3.3 percent to 1.25 soles
after silver hit a 31-year high in New York.  Candente Copper
Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration company, rose 2.3 percent
to $1.77 after announcing it began a feasibility study at its
Canariaco Norte copper deposit. Cia. Minera Milpo (MILPOC1 PE),
a zinc and lead producer controlled by Sao Paulo-based
Votorantim Metais Ltda., gained 1.3 percent to 6.87 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  